===== acos =====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cmath>
double acos( double arg );
</source>
}}

The acos() function returns the arc cosine of ''arg'', which will be in the range [0, pi]. ''arg'' should be between -1 and 1. If ''arg'' is outside this range, acos() returns NAN and raises a floating-point exception.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/asin|asin]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/atan|atan]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/atan2|atan2]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/cos|cos]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/cosh|cosh]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/sin|sin]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/sinh|sinh]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/tan|tan]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/tanh|tanh]]

[[Category:C++ Programming|{{SUBPAGENAME}}]]

===== asin =====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <cmath>
double asin( double arg );
</source>
}}

The asin() function returns the arc sine of ''arg'', which will be in the range [-pi/2, +pi/2]. ''arg'' should be between -1 and 1. If ''arg'' is outside this range, asin() returns NAN and raises a floating-point exception.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/acos|acos]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/atan|atan]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/atan2|atan2]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/cos|cos]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/cosh|cosh]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/sin|sin]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/sinh|sinh]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/tan|tan]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/tanh|tanh]]

[[Category:C++ Programming|{{SUBPAGENAME}}]]

